LOKOJA â€“ The Kogi State Governor, Alhaji Yahaya Bello, has appointed Justice Josiah Mejebi as Acting Chief Judge of the state. Performing the swearing in, Monday in Lokoja, Gov. Bello charged the jurist to discharge justice without fear or favour. While describing the Chief Judge as a man of impeccable character, urged him to sustain the feat already attained by his predecessors. Speaking at the occasion, Justice Josiah Mejebi promised to ensure quick dispensation of justice,and to uphold the tenet of an unbiased judiciary under his watch.